2. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper mentions the potential application of Obj-GloVe in text-to-image synthesis, which falls under the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses the GloVe word embedding method, which is a popular machine learning technique for natural language processing, and applies it to the visual domain. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new method for exploiting co-occurrence information among visual objects, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with visual objects and their embeddings, which is a topic that falls under the multimedia category.
